𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟏𝟑 𝐨𝐟 𝟗𝟎𝐃𝐚𝐲𝐬𝐎𝐟𝐃𝐞𝐯𝐎𝐩𝐬
𝙅𝙞𝙧𝙖 𝙈𝙖𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙧𝙘𝙡𝙖𝙨𝙨 
About Jira and its powerful role in project management.
𝙎𝙘𝙧𝙪𝙢--> Use Scrum if your team wants to track the state of tasks, sprint cycles, and regular reviews.
𝙆𝘼𝙉𝘽𝘼𝙉--> Use Kanban if your team prefers continuous delivery and flexible priorities.
➡️ 𝙆𝙚𝙮 𝘾𝙤𝙣𝙘𝙚𝙥𝙩𝙨 𝙞𝙣 𝙅𝙞𝙧𝙖
 𝙀𝙥𝙞𝙘 --> Big goal --> Tracks large features or goals
 𝙎𝙩𝙤𝙧𝙮--> User need --> Describes functionality from user’s pov
 𝙏𝙖𝙨𝙠--> Action step --> Small to-do item assigned to someone
 
➡️ 𝙄𝙣𝙩𝙚𝙜𝙧𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣 𝙤𝙛 :
1. 𝙅𝙞𝙧𝙖 + 𝙎𝙡𝙖𝙘𝙠: Get real-time updates on issue creation, assignment, and changes directly in Slack channels.
 2. 𝙅𝙞𝙧𝙖 + 𝙂𝙞𝙩𝙃𝙪𝙗: Sync commit messages and PRs with Jira issues for better traceability.
➡️ 𝙒𝙚𝙗𝙝𝙤𝙤𝙠𝙨 𝙞𝙣 𝙅𝙞𝙧𝙖
A webhook allows Jira to notify external services when certain events happen (like progress updates). It’s a way to connect Jira with other tools like Slack or CI/CD systems.
 
➡️ 𝙎𝙡𝙖𝙘𝙠 𝘼𝙪𝙩𝙤𝙢𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣 𝙎𝙩𝙚𝙥𝙨 (𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙚𝙞𝙫𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙥𝙧𝙤𝙜𝙧𝙚𝙨𝙨 𝙣𝙤𝙩𝙞𝙛𝙞𝙘𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣𝙨):
1. Go to Jira Settings > System > Webhooks.
2. Create a new webhook with the Slack Incoming Webhook URL.
3. Select events like "Issue Created", "Issue Updated", etc.
4. Test the webhook to ensure Slack receives updates.
5. Customize your Slack message formatting using JSON payloads for clarity.
